# Docs And Tests Rules

## Documentation Sync
Update docs in the same task when changing:
- behavior
- flows
- interfaces
- data shapes
- architecture boundaries
- env or runbook steps
- release procedures

Use `docs/docs-policy.md` to decide whether to update an existing doc or create a new one.
If no doc needs updating, explicitly report why the existing docs already cover the change.

## Testing Sync
### New feature
Add:
- happy-path coverage
- at least one edge case
- at least one failure-path test

### Bug fix
Add or update a regression test.

### Contract change
Add or update integration-style tests.

### Release-impacting change
Review `docs/12-release-smoke-checklist.md`.

### Validation reporting
For code-affecting tasks, explicitly report:
- whether `npm test` was run
- whether `npm run test:live` was run
- whether online smoke was run
- if any layer was skipped, why it was skipped

## Done Criteria
Do not mark the task done unless:
- docs are updated
- tests are updated when required
- validation commands were executed, or the blocker is explicitly reported
